Came in on 11/24/19 at 1:30pm. I come in every sunday to buy a bag of veranda coffee and have it ground turkish for my uncle. A few times in the past there has been miscommunication about how I wanted the coffee ground, but the staff gladly ran the ground through their machine once more to make it Turkish. No conflicts would occur. However today I went in and there was clearly a new employee behind the register who didnt hear me clearly, I clarified by saying as small as possible to make it easier for him to understand. He misunderstood and ran it through as paper, not a big deal. I asked for him to run it through again. The shift manager comes and starts giving me an attitude, saying they're unable to reground because it will clog the machine. Now having seen it done multiple times before she is clearly lying, so I asked for it to be done anyway. It was clear that she clogged the machine out of spite, to make her point.  Overall upsetting for a new employee to have such a toxic shift manager, and sad to see said manager act in an immature way.
